This workflow is designed to create 300dpi 24"x36" inch posters that you can take directly to a poster printer for art you can hang on your walls.

Approximate rendering times:

RTX3070 - 30 minutes
t4 - 1 hour
a10 - 20 minutes
a100 - 12 minutes

You'll want to use fixed seeds in your creation process, otherwise when you upscale it will render something different.

You'll want to keep upscaling turned off until you are happy with your design.

While I could have used a turbo model for the upscaling, my experience has found that turbo doesn't do as well as the original checkpoint.  Feel free to experiment, though.

If you find this workflow useful, consider buying me a cup of coffee:
https://www.buymeacoffee.com/gcyvtilmx

Clark Glenn Davis aka Verevolf
February 10, 2024
